,"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior femoral cutaneous nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is the major sensory branch of the sacral plexus. It provides sensory innervation to the skin of the posterior thigh and part of the perineum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESciatic nerve\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a mixed nerve providing both motor and sensory innervation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPudendal nerve\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily involved in motor and sensory innervation of the perineum\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuperior gluteal nerve\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily a motor nerve supplying the gluteal muscles\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInferior gluteal nerve\u003C/strong\u003E - Also primarily a motor nerve supplying the gluteus maximus\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The posterior femoral cutaneous nerve is a major sensory branch of the sacral plexus.","The posterior femoral cutaneous nerve provides sensory innervation to the skin of the posterior thigh and part of the perineum."],"references":["Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Miniato MA, Black AC, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Back, Lumbosacral Trunk. [Updated 2023 Oct 12]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK539878/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63366"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17298"}},"stemMedia"